</node>
<node id="MIUI">
  <data key="d0">MIUI</data>
  <data key="d1">content</data>
  <data key="d2">MIUI is Xiaomi's previous mobile operating system, now replaced by Hyper OS, which has built a large active user base.&lt;SEP&gt;MIUI is a customized Android-based operating system developed by Xiaomi. Initially released in 2010, it accumulated the first batch of enthusiast users through forum interactions, establishing Xiaomi's unique fan culture.&lt;SEP&gt;MIUI是小米基于安卓深度定制的操作系统，通过论坛与极客用户互动积累了大量粉丝，成为小米生态的核心组成部分。&lt;SEP&gt;MIUI是小米公司的操作系统，为小米手机提供用户交互界面和服务，后被澎湃OS取代。</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d53115d4331a6108b6e778bee3c915f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fdb937e9e57716d51ecc291d0e052dfc</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779417069</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mi Phone 1">
  <data key="d0">Mi Phone 1</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Mi Phone 1 is the first smartphone released by Xiaomi in August 2011. Priced at 1,999 yuan, it featured flagship-level specifications including a Qualcomm dual-core processor and 1GB RAM.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d53115d4331a6108b6e778bee3c915f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1779357459</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Redmi">
  <data key="d0">Redmi</data>
  <data key="d1">artifact</data>
  <data key="d2">Redmi is a budget smartphone brand launched by Xiaomi in 2013 at an extremely low price of 799 yuan, which helped popularize smartphones in China and eliminate counterfeit phone manufacturers.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d53115d4331a6108b6e778bee3c915f</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
